<body>
	
<header>
<div id="instruction">	
		Which of the following do you think would be good advice to a candidate about to do IELTS speaking Phase 2? Click yes or no against the statements.
</div>		
</header>
	
<section id="body">
<div id="outer">
  <img class="rightFloat" src="../media/set6_03.jpg" mode="1" id="1001"/>
<div id="content">
  <ol>
    <li id="q1">Talk confidently.</li>
		<a id="a1"><b>Yes</b></a><tab/><tab/><a id="a2"><b>No</b></a>
    
	<p class="linespace"></p>
    <li id="q2">Feel free to correct yourself if you make a mistake.</li>
		<a id="a3"><b>Yes</b></a><tab/><tab/><a id="a4"><b>No</b></a>
    
	<p class="linespace"></p>
    <li id="q3">Tell the examiner you are very nervous.</li>
		<a id="a5"><b>Yes</b></a><tab/><tab/><a id="a6"><b>No</b></a>
    
	<p class="linespace"></p>
    <li id="q4">Smile and look directly at the examiner.</li>
		<a id="a7"><b>Yes</b></a><tab/><tab/><a id="a8"><b>No</b></a>
    
	<p class="linespace"></p>
    <li id="q5">Think of enough material to talk about until the examiner stops you.</li>
		<a id="a9"><b>Yes</b></a><tab/><tab/><a id="a10"><b>No</b></a>
    
	<p class="linespace"></p>
    <li id="q6">Show interest in the topic.</li>
		<a id="a11"><b>Yes</b></a><tab/><tab/><a id="a12"><b>No</b></a>
    
	<p class="linespace"></p>
    <li id="q7">Learn by heart several short speeches on topics which may come up.</li>
		<a id="a13"><b>Yes</b></a><tab/><tab/><a id="a14"><b>No</b></a>
    
	<p class="linespace"></p>
    <li id="q8">Don't speak about something if you know nothing about it.</li>
		<a id="a15"><b>Yes</b></a><tab/><tab/><a id="a16"><b>No</b></a>
  </ol>
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section id="fb1">
  <p class="feedbacktext">Confidence is a positive thing and will make what you say more interesting.</p>
</section>

<section id="fb2">
  <p class="feedbacktext">
    Correcting yourself shows that you are aware of the mistake and that you know the correct language too. This is positive.
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb3">
  <p class="feedbacktext">
    The examiner expects you to be a bit nervous. There is no need to say it.
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb4">
  <p class="feedbacktext">
    This is a friendly thing to do and helps establish good communication.
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb5">
  <p class="feedbacktext">
    In Phase 2 it is good to talk until the examiner stops you.
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb6">
  <p class="feedbacktext">
    If you show interest, then what you say will be more interesting to the examiner.
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb7">
  <p class="feedbacktext">
    Learning by heart will not help you in this test. It may cause you to lose marks.
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb8">
  <p class="feedbacktext">
    You are not expected to know everything, but you should express an opinion or some thoughts on everything you are asked.
  </p>
</section>

